# E-Shop Frontend

React 19 + Vite + React Router + Axios. Plain JSX (no TypeScript). Match existing pages before introducing new patterns.

## Layout

```
eshop-frontend/src/
  services/api.js       # Axios client + domain services
  context/AuthContext.jsx
  components/ProtectedRoute.jsx
  pages/<Page>.jsx + <Page>.css
  App.jsx               # Routes + ProtectedRoute wrappers
```

## API layer

- Use named services from `../services/api` — never raw `fetch` or a second Axios instance.
- Backend base URL: `http://localhost:3000/api` (axios instance in `api.js`).
- JWT: request interceptor reads `localStorage.token`; 401 clears tokens and redirects to `/login`.
- **Payload shape:** read entity data from `response.data.data` (lists may use `.data.items`).
- **Errors:** `err.response?.data?.message || 'Human-readable fallback'`.

```javascript
// ✅ Page data fetch
const response = await cartService.get();
setCart(response.data.data);

// ✅ Error handling
catch (err) {
  setError(err.response?.data?.message || 'Failed to load cart');
}
```

Services: `authService`, `productsService`, `cartService`, `checkoutService`, `ordersService`.

## Auth & routing

- `useAuth()` from `AuthContext` for `user`, `login`, `logout`, `updateProfile`, `isAuthenticated`, `loading`.
- Protected screens: wrap route element in `<ProtectedRoute>` in `App.jsx`, not per-page redirects.
- After logout: `await logout(); navigate('/login')`.
- Post-login default: `/catalog`.

## Page component pattern

- Functional components; `export default` for the main page.
- State trio: `loading`, `error`, domain data (`useState`).
- Load in `useEffect` with an inner `async` function or a `loadX` helper called from handlers.
- Handlers: `handleSubmit`, `handleLogout`, `handleAddToCart` — call `e.preventDefault()` on forms.
- Import co-located styles: `import './PageName.css'`.
- Money display: `` `$${Number(amount).toFixed(2)}` ``.

```jsx
const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
const [error, setError] = useState(null);

useEffect(() => {
  const load = async () => {
    try {
      const response = await ordersService.list();
      setOrders(response.data.data || []);
    } catch (err) {
      setError(err.response?.data?.message || 'Failed to load orders');
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };
  load();
}, []);
```

## Styling

- One CSS file per page; class prefix matches the feature (`catalog-`, `cart-`, `checkout-`, `ps-` for payment return).
- Page shell: `*-page` / `*-shell`; actions: `*-btn` or `btn` + `ghost`/`primary`.
- Reuse global form classes from auth (`form-group`, `btn btn-primary`) on profile-style pages.

## Checkout / Saferpay

- Card flow: `checkoutService.initiatePayment` → store token in `sessionStorage` key `saferpay.paymentToken` → `window.location.href = redirectUrl`.
- Return routes: `/payment/success|fail|abort` via `<PaymentReturn outcome="…" />`.
- On return: `checkoutService.confirmPayment(token)`; guard double-call with `useRef` (StrictMode-safe).
- Clear token from sessionStorage after confirm or abort.

## Conventions

- Prefer `useNavigate()` for in-app navigation; full redirect only for external payment URLs.
- Complex UIs: small subcomponents in the same file (`Loading`, `Success`) before adding new folders.
- Named exports only for route variants (e.g. `OrdersList` alongside default `OrderDetails`).
- Match quote style of the file you edit (project mixes `'` and `"`).
